            <h1>Tagged Questions</h1>


<div id="tabs">
        <a href="/tags/convolution/info" title="information about this tag">info</a>
        <a class="youarehere" href="/questions/tagged/convolution?sort=newest&amp;pageSize=15" title="The most recently asked questions">newest</a>
        <a href="/questions/tagged/convolution?sort=frequent&amp;pageSize=15" title="Questions with the most links">frequent</a>
        <a href="/questions/tagged/convolution?sort=votes&amp;pageSize=15" title="Questions with the most votes">votes</a>
        <a href="/questions/tagged/convolution?sort=active&amp;pageSize=15" title="Questions that have recent activity">active</a>
        <a href="/questions/tagged/convolution?sort=unanswered&amp;pageSize=15" title="Questions that have no upvoted answers">unanswered</a>
</div>
        </div>
        <div class="question">


            <div class="welovestackoverflow" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <div style="float: left;">
                        <p>
A mathematical operation that combines two signals to generate a third signal.  Convolution often arises in audio processing (e.g., filtering, reverb) and image processing (e.g., blurring, edge detection).                         </p>
                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                            <a title="tag wiki" href="/tags/convolution/info">learn more&hellip;</a>
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="top answerers and askers in this tag" href="/tags/convolution/topusers">top users</a> 
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="common, alternate spellings or phrasings for this tag" href="/tags/convolution/synonyms">synonyms</a>
                                                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

